	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><add>German</add> With the wish for your happiness&#44; and that<lb/> you may declare yourself my friend openly as you are<lb/> in secret&#44;</p>
				<p><persName role="author">I. Kalisch</persName>.</p>
				<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
				<p rend="align(center)"><hi rend="underline">Announcement</hi></p>
				<p rend="indent(1)">In order that no complaint be made against me and<lb/> other rabbis that we objected to the <hi rend="underline">Get</hi> which was given here<lb/> in <placeName>Cleveland</placeName>&#44; and lest it be said that we transgressed the Edict<lb/> of the rabbis not to leave matters of divorce to gentiles&#44; that is<lb/> why I publicly announce that since the one who arranged the<lb/> <hi rend="underline">Get</hi> did not understand the nature of the laws on marriage and<lb/> divorce&#44; his actions and words are not to be considered&#44; and<lb/> with regard to this sort of <hi rend="underline">Get</hi> there is no applicability of the<lb/> law about spreading false rumors &#91;See <persName>Maharik</persName> &#167;36&#44;<lb/> and other legalists&#93;</p>
				<p>And the following is evidence that this man had<lb/> no knowledge of the nature of divorce</p>
				<list type="ordered">
				<head></head>
				<item n="1"> He did not know that it was necessary to ask the<lb/> man whether he had not vowed to his wife not to divorce<lb/> her&#44; in which case it is first necessary to free him<lb/> from his oath&#44; lest he be caught in the net of a false<lb/> oath&#44; as I have written in my first letter.</item>
				<item n="2"> <del>There was</del> The court had become invalidated</item>
				<item n="3"> Further proof is in the fact that the one who arranged<lb/> the divorce had written in this magazine that he had<lb/> found no law about names of new places&#44; while&#44;<lb/> as a matter of fact&#44; there are piles of such laws</item>
				</list>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>If the matter had come before me&#44; I would have<lb/> investigated very closely&#44; and asked scholars<lb/> what the legal name of the place should be.  This<lb/> is what any sensible man would do&#44; and not<lb/> like this perverse and stupid fellow about<lb/> whom it is said &#34;and it happened when<lb/> the judges judged&#34;&#42;&#44; and about when the<lb/> sages said that he is the kind that compares<lb/> himself to <persName>Elazar ben Arach</persName>&#44; as superior<lb/> to everyone else.</p>
				<p>These are the words of</p>
				<p><persName role="author">Israel</persName> son of <persName>Simha Bunas Kalisch</persName></p>
				<p>Head of Court of <placeName>Cleveland</placeName></p>
				<p><date>&#40;Ellul 1854&#41;</date></p>
				<p>&#42; The reference is &#34;each man did what seemed good<lb/> in his eyes&#34;</p>
		</body>
